The paper discusses the application of Conditional Restricted Boltzmann Machines (CRBMs) to structured output prediction problems, which are typically addressed in the sub-fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also mentions specific applications such as collaborative filtering, classification, and modeling motion capture data, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.CL. Additionally, the paper proposes improved learning algorithms for CRBMs, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
